In the ''{{ill|Un'yōshi|ja|雲陽誌|12=draft}}'', a regional record compiled during the Edo period in the {{ill|Matsue Domain|ja|松江藩|12=draft}}, the section on {{ill|Matsuzaki Shrine|ja|松崎神社|12=draft}} mentions, "The ancestral deity of this shrine is called Mikahayahi, the god of the stars."<ref>{{cite book|editor=Ashida Ikuto |title=Great Japanese Gazetteer Series|volume=Vol. 27|publisher=Yuzankaku |year=1930 |chapter=Un'yōshi Volume 1, Shimane District|section=Matsuzaki Shrine|page=24|doi=10.11501/1194083|url={{NDLDC|1194083/19}} }} ({{ill|National Diet Library Digital Collections|ja|国立国会図書館デジタルコレクション|12=draft}})</ref>

