{{Infobox deity|parents={{ill|Kagu-tsuchi|qid=Q1640658}}|offspring={{ill|Takemikazuchi|qid=Q1502690}}}}{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11574224]] Wikidata name: (none) [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 08:10, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} [[Image:Descendants of Izanagi and Izanami.svg|thumb|right|250px|Kami born from Izanagi and Izanami ([[Media:Descendants of Izanagi and Izanami.svg|View in SVG format (supported browsers only)]])]] : '''Mikahayahi''' '''no Kami''' (甕速日神) is a deity in [[:en:Japanese mythology|Japanese mythology]], born during the [[:en:Kamiumi|kami birth (Shinto)]] when [[:en:Izanagi|Izanagi]] decapitated [[:en:Kagu-tsuchi|Kagutsuchi]]. Mikahayahi no Kami emerged from the blood that splattered onto rocks from the base of the [[:en:Totsuka-no-Tsurugi|Totsuka-no-Tsurugi]] known as "[[:en:Ame-no-ohabari|Ame-no-ohabari]]."
According to the ''[[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]]'', Mikahayahi no Kami is considered an ancestor of {{ill|Takemikazuchi|ja|武甕雷男神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takemikazuchi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. However, the text also states that {{ill|Hisahayahi no Kami|ja|樋速日神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hisahayahi no Kami|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, Mikahayahi no Kami, and Takemikazuchi were born simultaneously.
In the ''{{ill|Un'yōshi|ja|雲陽誌|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Un'yōshi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}'', a regional record compiled during the Edo period in the [[:en:Matsue Domain|Matsue Domain]], the section on {{ill|Matsuzaki Shrine|ja|松崎神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsuzaki Shrine|qq=|1=Matsusaki Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11530226}} mentions, "The ancestral deity of this shrine is called Mikahayahi, the god of the stars."<ref>{{cite book|editor=Ashida Ikuto |title=Great Japanese Gazetteer Series|volume=Vol. 27|publisher=Yuzankaku |year=1930 |chapter=Un'yōshi Volume 1, Shimane District|section=Matsuzaki Shrine|page=24|doi=10.11501/1194083|url={{NDLDC|1194083/19}} }} ({{ill|National Diet Library Digital Collections|ja|国立国会図書館デジタルコレクション|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/National Diet Library Digital Collections|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 国立国会図書館|1=National Diet Library|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q477675}})</ref>
