'''Mikahayahi''' '''no Kami''' (甕速日神) is a deity in {{ill|Japanese mythology|en|Japanese mythology|qid=Q814158|lt=Japanese mythology|1=Japanese mythology}}, born during the {{ill|Kamiumi|en|Kamiumi|qid=Q3545159|lt=kami birth (Shinto)|1=Kamiumi}} when {{ill|Izanagi|en|Izanagi|qid=Q813858|lt=Izanagi|1=Izanagi}} decapitated {{ill|Kagu-tsuchi|en|Kagu-tsuchi|qid=Q1640658|lt=Kagutsuchi|1=Kagu-tsuchi}}. Mikahayahi no Kami emerged from the blood that splattered onto rocks from the base of the {{ill|Totsuka-no-Tsurugi|en|Totsuka-no-Tsurugi|qid=Q2628318|lt=Totsuka-no-Tsurugi|1=Totsuka-no-Tsurugi}} known as "{{ill|Ame-no-ohabari|en|Ame-no-ohabari|qid=Q10939046|lt=Ame-no-ohabari|1=Ame-no-ohabari}}."

According to the ''{{ill|Nihon Shoki|en|Nihon Shoki|qid=Q813935|lt=Nihon Shoki|1=Nihon Shoki}}'', Mikahayahi no Kami is considered an ancestor of {{ill|Takemikazuchi|ja|武甕雷男神|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takemikazuchi|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. However, the text also states that {{ill|Hisahayahi no Kami|ja|樋速日神|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hisahayahi no Kami|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, Mikahayahi no Kami, and Takemikazuchi were born simultaneously.

In the ''{{ill|Un'yōshi|ja|雲陽誌|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Un'yōshi|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}'', a regional record compiled during the Edo period in the {{ill|Matsue Domain|en|Matsue Domain|qid=Q1017072|lt=Matsue Domain|1=Matsue Domain}}, the section on {{ill|Matsuzaki Shrine|ja|松崎神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsuzaki Shrine|1=Matsusaki Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11530226}} mentions, "The ancestral deity of this shrine is called Mikahayahi, the god of the stars."<ref>{{cite book|editor=Ashida Ikuto |title=Great Japanese Gazetteer Series|volume=Vol. 27|publisher=Yuzankaku |year=1930 |chapter=Un'yōshi Volume 1, Shimane District|section=Matsuzaki Shrine|page=24|doi=10.11501/1194083|url={{NDLDC|1194083/19}} }} ({{ill|National Diet Library Digital Collections|ja|国立国会図書館デジタルコレクション|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/National Diet Library Digital Collections|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 国立国会図書館|1=National Diet Library|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q477675}})</ref>

